  "prompt": "My husband likes to watch movies a lot. I don't. What should I do?",
  "response": "It's important to find a balance and spend quality time together while also respecting each other's interests and preferences. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Compromise:** Occasionally, you might watch a movie with your husband, and in turn, he might engage in an activity you enjoy.\n\n2. **Shared Activities:** Identify activities that both of you enjoy. This could be board games, cooking together, going for walks, or any other shared interests.\n\n3. **Respect Individual Interests:** Allow each other some personal time to engage in individual hobbies. It's healthy to have time apart to pursue personal interests.\n\n4. **Participate in Discussions:** Even if you don't enjoy watching movies, you could show interest in discussing them. Ask your husband about the plot, characters, or why he enjoyed a particular film.\n\n5. **Find Common Ground:** Sometimes, a genre or type of movie might appeal to you. Experiment with different kinds of movies to see if there is something you both enjoy.\n\n6. **Shared Movie Night:** Set aside specific times for 'movie night,' where together you pick movies that you feel more comfortable watching. \n\n7. **Communication:** Make sure to communicate your feelings and preferences openly with your husband. Express your needs and listen to his as well.\n\nRemember that in any relationship, both partners should feel heard and valued. Balance and mutual respect are key.",
